

1).Use Terraform to create EKS cluster and configure Ingress controller and resource to deploy the application and 
configure the RDS database for the backend configuration of the application.

2).Use an appropriate different terraform block configuration.such backend,provider,variable,provisioner etc.
Include any necessary configuration variables or files.

3).Install Prometheus and grafana through the helm to monitor the Application.

4).Use AWS lamda services that should upload resources and application logs  automatically to s3 bucket.

5).Provide a README.md file that explains how to deploy the infrastructure.

6).Detailed step by step guide  to access and test applications
